WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.300 --> 00:00:07.906
Rescue station one.
This is sheriff clemmons.

2
00:00:07.930 --> 00:00:10.816
All available fire and
rescue to Patricia's cocktails.

3
00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:12.630
I don't know what the fuck is going on!

4
00:01:06.230 --> 00:01:07.440
Every time.

5
00:02:00.410 --> 00:02:01.450
Patricia.

6
00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:05.380
You said I should stop by?

7
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:09.540
Of course. Yeah. of course. come on in.

8
00:02:27.650 --> 00:02:28.980
Should I open this bottle?

9
00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:33.280
Yeah. We're all drinking white.
but if you want to. feel free.

10
00:02:34.450 --> 00:02:36.290
- Cool.
- Just in the kitchen.

11
00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:51.236
He snores when he's laying on his
back. He snores when he's on his side.

12
00:02:51.260 --> 00:02:53.486
I swear to god. if he
doesn't stop snoring. I'm just…

13
00:02:53.510 --> 00:02:54.950
I'm gonna smother him with a pillow.

14
00:02:55.510 --> 00:02:58.696
My dad snored so loud my mom
made him sleep on the couch.

15
00:02:58.720 --> 00:03:00.236
and you could still hear him…

16
00:03:00.260 --> 00:03:02.786
- My ex was the worst snorer.
- …all the way up...

17
00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:05.666
and I'm telling you. it was the worst.

18
00:03:05.690 --> 00:03:07.780
Not just the smell. and
it smelled pretty bad…

19
00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:17.910
Please don't open that.

20
00:03:20.370 --> 00:03:21.960
Here. Here it is.

21
00:03:24.370 --> 00:03:27.250
- I think it's clean.
- Thank you.

22
00:03:27.960 --> 00:03:29.170
I don't think we've met.

23
00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:33.566
I just moved here a few months
ago from Portsmouth. I'm Shelby.

24
00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:35.180
- Patricia.
- Hi.

25
00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:40.736
Lenore's the only person I know here.

26
00:03:40.760 --> 00:03:44.060
hence the reason I'm already
on my third glass of wine.

27
00:03:45.770 --> 00:03:47.190
What about you? Who do you know?

28
00:03:47.900 --> 00:03:50.536
I graduated with most of them.

29
00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:51.876
but I'm usually pretty busy.

30
00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:54.070
so I don't often make it to these things.

31
00:03:55.740 --> 00:03:57.370
Can I ask you about it?

32
00:03:59.070 --> 00:04:00.070
What?

33
00:04:00.870 --> 00:04:02.846
The girls that died here.

34
00:04:02.870 --> 00:04:05.620
You… you must have all
gone to school together.

35
00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:07.896
Did I know them?

36
00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:08.920
Yeah.

37
00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:11.830
I was almost one of them.

38
00:04:13.800 --> 00:04:15.220
No.

39
00:04:15.710 --> 00:04:16.936
Yeah.

40
00:04:16.960 --> 00:04:18.986
And what happened? I'm sor…

41
00:04:19.010 --> 00:04:21.486
I shouldn't be asking you that. I
mean. it must be so hard to talk about.

42
00:04:21.510 --> 00:04:22.930
It started with the calls…

43
00:04:23.510 --> 00:04:27.786
Weird breathing and hang-ups.
and then one night I was alone.

44
00:04:27.810 --> 00:04:31.036
My god. Did he come to your house?

45
00:04:31.060 --> 00:04:32.440
The boogeyman?

46
00:04:33.110 --> 00:04:34.780
Holy shit.

47
00:04:36.030 --> 00:04:38.836
I heard someone
downstairs and I just knew...

48
00:04:38.860 --> 00:04:41.386
- your gut instinct.
- Yeah. Exa… that's right.

49
00:04:41.410 --> 00:04:44.676
And I just thought. is
this when I... excuse me.

50
00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:47.386
- I'm sorry.
- No. It's fine.

51
00:04:47.410 --> 00:04:50.476
No. I… it looks like she really got ya.

52
00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:51.976
- Yeah.
- Shoot.

53
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.000
All right. well…

54
00:04:53.500 --> 00:04:56.026
I'm gonna run to the
bathroom real quick. but then

55
00:04:56.050 --> 00:04:58.236
- I have questions for you.
- Yeah. okay.

56
00:04:58.260 --> 00:04:59.340
Yeah.

57
00:05:08.350 --> 00:05:09.350
Okay.

58
00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:15.546
We've all heard it a few times. I
mean. how many times can you lie?

59
00:05:15.570 --> 00:05:17.456
You know. they even
checked the phone records

60
00:05:17.480 --> 00:05:19.926
- and they proved she never got the calls.
- That's right.

61
00:05:19.950 --> 00:05:22.006
Twenty-five years she's
been telling that story.

62
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:24.806
She'll tell anyone who will
listen. It's honestly so pathetic.

63
00:05:24.830 --> 00:05:27.056
- Crazy.
- She's. like. on another level.

64
00:05:27.080 --> 00:05:28.870
- I know.
- She is certifiable.

65
00:05:29.450 --> 00:05:31.016
- You're so right. kris.
- She's nuts. Yes.

66
00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:33.670
It was the first thing she
did when she got here.

67
00:05:41.010 --> 00:05:42.770
Do you think you could
grab a picture of us?

68
00:05:43.340 --> 00:05:44.840
Yeah. Sure.

69
00:05:46.510 --> 00:05:47.906
- Great.
- All right.

70
00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:49.826
Come on. ladies. Everybody get together.

71
00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:51.116
Yeah. Back there. Come on.

72
00:05:51.140 --> 00:05:52.456
Get my best side.

73
00:05:52.480 --> 00:05:54.150
- All my friends together.
- Yes.

74
00:05:54.810 --> 00:05:55.980
Say wine and cheese.

75
00:05:58.030 --> 00:05:59.280
There we go.

76
00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:03.216
- Well…
- you see. we only have. like. two.

77
00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:04.426
- I know.
- That's a good one.

78
00:06:04.450 --> 00:06:05.450
- Later on.
- Later.

79
00:07:33.200 --> 00:07:35.870
"What don't you love about yourself?"

80
00:07:38.210 --> 00:07:46.210
I care too much what other people think.

81
00:08:10.370 --> 00:08:14.516
"Feeling like you could die
tomorrow and no one would notice?"

82
00:08:14.540 --> 00:08:16.420
Well. that could be.

83
00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:20.210
"But the right party can change that."

84
00:08:22.540 --> 00:08:26.540
"The perfect hostess exudes confidence.

85
00:08:27.380 --> 00:08:29.130
effortless and elegant."

86
00:08:30.550 --> 00:08:31.640
"Elegant."

87
00:08:38.770 --> 00:08:43.190
"Suddenly. everyone knows you as
someone who throws great parties."

88
00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:48.860
All it takes is one to
change people's minds.

89
00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:53.160
"All it takes is one great
party to change your life."

90
00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:07.356
Rosemary. here are the supplies.

91
00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:10.760
And Dale. you're gonna need a
turntable 'cause you're gonna dj.

92
00:09:11.970 --> 00:09:13.026
I've never done that before.

93
00:09:13.050 --> 00:09:14.486
You're gonna have them all dancing.

94
00:09:14.510 --> 00:09:16.786
There won't be a single
moment of silence.

95
00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:19.286
Each song will blend
seamlessly to the next.

96
00:09:19.310 --> 00:09:22.576
Everyone's gonna talk about that
night they danced at sunset cocktails

97
00:09:22.600 --> 00:09:24.520
and that is all gonna be down to you.

98
00:09:25.650 --> 00:09:27.586
Okay. maybe you should hire someone.

99
00:09:27.610 --> 00:09:28.820
You'll be fine.

100
00:10:26.750 --> 00:10:30.026
Okay. so we're gonna put
the floral arrangements up here.

101
00:10:30.050 --> 00:10:32.106
I want that to be the
first thing people see.

102
00:10:32.130 --> 00:10:35.616
and we're gonna need to move some
tables out of here for the dance floor.

103
00:10:35.640 --> 00:10:37.440
or do you think that'll
make it look too big?

104
00:10:38.060 --> 00:10:39.116
I don't know.

105
00:10:39.140 --> 00:10:41.456
Okay. Well. what's next?

106
00:10:41.480 --> 00:10:44.480
I got catering. which I'm
thinking about kind of…

107
00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.886
- Totally my fault.
- Yeah. I'm starving.

108
00:10:56.910 --> 00:10:58.346
All right. Me too.

109
00:10:58.370 --> 00:11:00.096
We were thinking about…
well. let's get some oysters.

110
00:11:00.120 --> 00:11:01.346
- This is cute.
- Thank you.

111
00:11:01.370 --> 00:11:02.886
And I know you like shrimp cocktails.

112
00:11:02.910 --> 00:11:05.390
- so we could get a bit of everything.
- Yeah. shrimp is good.

113
00:11:06.670 --> 00:11:09.226
I don't know. we could
all get soup if we want.

114
00:11:09.250 --> 00:11:10.436
I'll probably get a burger.

115
00:11:10.460 --> 00:11:11.460
Hello.

116
00:11:15.010 --> 00:11:16.236
So I'm not sure if you heard.

117
00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:19.236
but I'm throwing a party
here tomorrow night.

118
00:11:19.260 --> 00:11:20.970
Do you mean the municipal event?

119
00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:26.036
Yeah. kris. the city's sponsoring
it. but I'm the chair and it's my party.

120
00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:28.860
so you're more than welcome to come.

121
00:11:29.610 --> 00:11:32.006
But I'd rsvp 'cause space is pretty limited

122
00:11:32.030 --> 00:11:34.926
and we're expecting a lot of people.

123
00:11:34.950 --> 00:11:38.160
Everybody's going to bill Rooney's
birthday at the elks lodge tomorrow.

124
00:11:41.490 --> 00:11:42.830
Bill's having a party?

125
00:11:46.040 --> 00:11:49.356
Well. that's actually a relief
'cause. what with all the tourists.

126
00:11:49.380 --> 00:11:52.470
I was worried that we'd have
to turn people away at the doors.

127
00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:54.670
I think you'll be okay.

128
00:11:57.550 --> 00:11:58.800
Enjoy your lunch.

129
00:12:00.390 --> 00:12:01.930
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

130
00:12:06.980 --> 00:12:08.980
No one is going to that.

131
00:12:11.060 --> 00:12:12.060
Seriously.

132
00:12:41.720 --> 00:12:44.906
I mean. there were probably
800 songs on that list.

133
00:12:44.930 --> 00:12:48.166
It's like she wrote down every
song she's ever heard in her life.

134
00:12:48.190 --> 00:12:49.270
And then she...

135
00:13:00.410 --> 00:13:03.250
Where are we with
rsvps for sunset cocktails?

136
00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:11.170
Zero people.

137
00:13:12.420 --> 00:13:14.880
Why'd you even hand me
this? Just say no one's rsvp'd.

138
00:13:17.590 --> 00:13:18.590
I didn't want to.

139
00:13:21.010 --> 00:13:24.810
The elks lodge isn't permitted to have
more than 30 nonmembers at a time.

140
00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:30.076
Call Glen. Tell him bill Rooney's
big birthday tonight is canceled.

141
00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:32.036
unless he wants me to
unleash hell on their little club

142
00:13:32.060 --> 00:13:34.150
when their liquor
license is up for renewal.

143
00:14:19.110 --> 00:14:21.820
Okay. loftis. Let's waste my time.

144
00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:28.990
Mayor called to see if
you found that old lady yet.

145
00:14:31.330 --> 00:14:34.016
Driscoll. do you think I'm
here for my own entertainment?

146
00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:36.960
I mean. it's not like I'm
back here watching footloose.

147
00:14:37.920 --> 00:14:38.920
Copy that.

148
00:15:06.700 --> 00:15:07.950
What the hell?

149
00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:48.620
Listen. I'm…

150
00:15:51.700 --> 00:15:54.846
I'm a little worried you're
putting too much into this thing.

151
00:15:55.960 --> 00:15:58.976
I didn't even understand
half the stuff on that supply list.

152
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:02.026
And might I suggest
a different headpiece?

153
00:16:02.050 --> 00:16:04.236
Rosemary. I don't need
your negativity right now.

154
00:16:04.260 --> 00:16:05.430
Just be supportive.

155
00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:10.930
I can't do anything right today.

156
00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:21.746
Check. check. one. two.

157
00:16:21.770 --> 00:16:23.956
Check. check. check. check one. two.

158
00:16:23.980 --> 00:16:26.086
Check. check. check one. two.

159
00:16:26.110 --> 00:16:29.426
Check. check. check. check one. two.

160
00:16:29.450 --> 00:16:31.596
Check. check. check one. two.

161
00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:32.676
Check. check...

162
00:16:32.700 --> 00:16:36.016
it started 15 minutes ago. Why
are you still saying. "check"?

163
00:16:36.040 --> 00:16:38.306
It's a surprisingly complicated system.

164
00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.686
- This is death. Dale.
- Okay. I'm gonna try something...

165
00:16:40.710 --> 00:16:43.606
hi there! Are you two
visiting from out of town?

166
00:16:43.630 --> 00:16:45.896
- Yeah.
- Great! We're just getting started.

167
00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:47.486
Okay. cool.

168
00:16:47.510 --> 00:16:50.616
- We'll circle back.
- No! Come. have a drink.

169
00:16:50.640 --> 00:16:55.390
Okay. So this is the dance floor.
if you wanna get your boogie on.

170
00:16:56.100 --> 00:16:57.270
Or not. you know.

171
00:16:58.770 --> 00:17:00.360
Have you met Dr. Calvin Morgan?

172
00:17:00.980 --> 00:17:02.836
I'm sure he'll have a great medical story.

173
00:17:02.860 --> 00:17:05.166
I'm off the clock tonight. Patricia.

174
00:17:05.190 --> 00:17:07.030
I've got a good one for you.

175
00:17:07.610 --> 00:17:09.006
It started in the foot.

176
00:17:09.030 --> 00:17:11.006
My god. Damn it!

177
00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:12.296
What? What?

178
00:17:12.320 --> 00:17:15.346
They're sitting right at the entrance
and I was trying to dress the room.

179
00:17:15.370 --> 00:17:16.540
you know what I'm saying?

180
00:17:17.160 --> 00:17:18.636
I got it.

181
00:17:18.660 --> 00:17:21.396
- All right. fuggos. let's go.
- No. no. no. no.

182
00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:23.050
You're out of deviled eggs.

183
00:17:23.790 --> 00:17:26.630
Okay. I'll get those… get the…

184
00:17:37.430 --> 00:17:38.430
To who?

185
00:17:48.780 --> 00:17:51.176
Well. Tom. I don't know where you are.

186
00:17:51.200 --> 00:17:53.450
but I am at the event…

187
00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:56.580
That you said you would be at!

188
00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:05.226
- Where are the good-looking people?
- I don't know.

189
00:18:05.250 --> 00:18:07.606
Did you see where the
good-looking people went?

190
00:18:07.630 --> 00:18:09.816
Has anyone seen the
good-looking people?

191
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.526
I see them. They're
at the top of the stairs.

192
00:18:12.550 --> 00:18:13.616
My god.

193
00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:16.236
- They are good-looking.
- Yes. Gorgeous.

194
00:18:16.260 --> 00:18:17.470
Yeah.

195
00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:20.720
Okay. come on!

196
00:18:21.440 --> 00:18:23.940
Party! All right.

197
00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:28.166
Affected by male-pattern baldness?

198
00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:31.400
Come see how we do
it... why is there an ad?

199
00:18:32.450 --> 00:18:33.506
I don't have premium.

200
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:36.780
- Good night. Patricia.
- What? No. it's just… it's too early.

201
00:18:46.040 --> 00:18:48.750
Let's get these bachelorettes shots!

202
00:18:59.930 --> 00:19:02.390
Crab cake? Crab cake?

203
00:19:03.810 --> 00:19:04.850
Crab cake?

204
00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:08.940
This is delicious.

205
00:19:09.530 --> 00:19:10.610
Is it your recipe?

206
00:19:11.280 --> 00:19:12.950
If I said yes. would you believe me?

207
00:19:13.650 --> 00:19:14.820
You shouldn't.

208
00:19:17.200 --> 00:19:19.200
I'm gonna get some more crab cakes.

209
00:19:20.200 --> 00:19:23.200
Seriously. what the fuck is on her head?

210
00:19:29.250 --> 00:19:30.960
Why are you always so nasty to me?

211
00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:33.220
Here we go.

212
00:19:33.880 --> 00:19:35.776
Look who gets to play victim again.

213
00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:38.696
You know what. kris. I don't
even care if you believe me.

214
00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:42.156
He came to my house. and
I hid under the bed. and he...

215
00:19:42.180 --> 00:19:43.430
you hid under the bed?

216
00:19:44.430 --> 00:19:46.890
My god. I… I didn't know that.

217
00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:49.440
Guys. she hid under her bed.

218
00:19:50.980 --> 00:19:52.296
How clever.

219
00:19:52.320 --> 00:19:55.240
I can't believe none of the
other girls thought to hide.

220
00:19:55.900 --> 00:19:58.046
Wait. they did.

221
00:19:58.070 --> 00:20:01.096
Samantha was stabbed
and then she hid in the dryer.

222
00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:04.516
Of course. he turned it on
and. well. she baked to death.

223
00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:09.920
And jen… Jen hid under her covered pool.
but he was already waiting there for her.

224
00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:14.260
But you… you hid under a bed.

225
00:20:15.010 --> 00:20:16.550
That must be his kryptonite.

226
00:20:17.430 --> 00:20:19.486
He can't look under beds.

227
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:24.116
I don't know why he didn't
find me. but he was there and I...

228
00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:25.350
just let it go!

229
00:20:26.270 --> 00:20:27.270
Let it go.

230
00:20:27.940 --> 00:20:30.940
My friends died.

231
00:20:31.650 --> 00:20:35.126
And you are just so.
so starved for attention

232
00:20:35.150 --> 00:20:36.990
that you had to make that about you.

233
00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:02.970
I'm sorry. I thought
this was the bathroom.

234
00:21:49.730 --> 00:21:51.150
Punch is served!

235
00:22:26.720 --> 00:22:28.350
Come on. let's dance.

236
00:22:29.430 --> 00:22:30.470
Sorry.

237
00:22:39.530 --> 00:22:41.950
This one in hingham has a den.

238
00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:44.490
I could use it as a craft room.

239
00:22:45.280 --> 00:22:48.716
How about a craft beer room? I've
been thinking about brewing my own.

240
00:22:48.740 --> 00:22:50.740
Funny way of asking for a divorce.

241
00:22:52.540 --> 00:22:53.920
Isn't your shift over?

242
00:22:56.340 --> 00:23:00.970
Well. loftis is convinced that

243
00:23:01.840 --> 00:23:04.050
there's some crazy old lady on the loose.

244
00:23:05.470 --> 00:23:07.310
Yeah. and she's waiting
for you to come home.

245
00:23:09.560 --> 00:23:10.650
I'm on my way.

246
00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:14.350
Can you pick up some
mint chocolate chip?

247
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:16.690
Already on it.

248
00:23:17.770 --> 00:23:20.230
Got a noise complaint at the salty whale.

249
00:23:22.650 --> 00:23:23.690
I don't care.

250
00:23:24.860 --> 00:23:27.030
It's Patricia's event.
Should I shut it down?

251
00:23:33.120 --> 00:23:35.960
No. No. I'll go myself.

252
00:24:47.360 --> 00:24:48.530
Sorry.

253
00:24:50.200 --> 00:24:51.780
I'm a little nervous.

254
00:24:52.330 --> 00:24:53.410
You've got this. baby.

255
00:24:58.040 --> 00:25:00.936
It means so much that
you're all here tonight.

256
00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:04.130
It's such a wonderful night for our town.

257
00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:08.880
I'm kind of at a loss for words honestly.

258
00:25:22.310 --> 00:25:26.520
"As I look around this room
at friends old and new…."

259
00:25:28.780 --> 00:25:29.950
I feel grateful.

260
00:25:32.070 --> 00:25:35.660
For there is always time to
change the course of history.

261
00:25:40.420 --> 00:25:44.090
"And tonight. tomorrow starts today."

262
00:25:47.590 --> 00:25:49.510
To new beginnings!

263
00:25:52.470 --> 00:25:54.116
Cheers.

264
00:25:54.140 --> 00:25:55.640
Cheers!

265
00:25:57.680 --> 00:25:59.850
Let's go down to the cove for the bonfire.

266
00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:02.560
Let's go. Patricia.

267
00:26:03.770 --> 00:26:05.246
Yeah. Patricia!

268
00:26:05.270 --> 00:26:06.756
Yeah. I'll just get some more punch.

269
00:26:06.780 --> 00:26:08.530
- Yeah. Let's go!
- Come on.

270
00:26:21.870 --> 00:26:22.870
What's your problem?

271
00:26:24.710 --> 00:26:27.800
I didn't understand
one word of that speech.

272
00:26:28.800 --> 00:26:34.446
I know that you asked me to be
supportive. but I have my qualms.

273
00:26:34.470 --> 00:26:35.680
That's all I'm gonna say.

274
00:26:37.350 --> 00:26:39.826
Bechir! Finally off duty?

275
00:26:39.850 --> 00:26:42.190
No. No. I…

276
00:26:42.770 --> 00:26:44.560
I had a noise complaint.

277
00:26:46.190 --> 00:26:47.860
Sorry. I guess people are having fun.

278
00:27:06.340 --> 00:27:07.420
Patricia.

279
00:27:09.550 --> 00:27:10.640
What…

280
00:27:13.930 --> 00:27:15.560
What the fuck are you doing?

281
00:27:35.740 --> 00:27:36.740
My god.

282
00:27:37.620 --> 00:27:38.620
My god.

283
00:27:39.160 --> 00:27:40.846
We tried to tell her.

284
00:27:40.870 --> 00:27:43.136
You had your qualms?

285
00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:46.210
- Why didn't you say anything?
- You told me to be supportive!

286
00:27:49.380 --> 00:27:51.170
What have I… what have I done?

287
00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:29.830
No. no. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

288
00:28:30.630 --> 00:28:31.630
No.

289
00:28:33.460 --> 00:28:34.460
My god.

290
00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:39.970
No. No.

291
00:28:47.140 --> 00:28:48.390
My god.

292
00:29:09.710 --> 00:29:12.936
You guys! What are you doing?

293
00:29:12.960 --> 00:29:14.800
Stop! Stop!

294
00:29:15.460 --> 00:29:16.816
Stop!

295
00:29:16.840 --> 00:29:18.220
Get back!

296
00:29:19.890 --> 00:29:21.946
Get back! Whoa. whoa.

297
00:29:21.970 --> 00:29:23.970
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!

298
00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:27.956
Whoa! Why is no one listening?

299
00:29:27.980 --> 00:29:29.730
I told you it's for…

300
00:29:31.810 --> 00:29:33.336
What the hell is going on?

301
00:29:33.360 --> 00:29:34.360
Just…

302
00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:36.900
Get them out! Save them!

303
00:29:37.690 --> 00:29:39.296
Come on. Everybody. stay here!

304
00:29:39.320 --> 00:29:42.176
Stay here! Hey! Excuse
me. hey! Get outta here!

305
00:29:42.200 --> 00:29:43.620
Shit. Come here.

306
00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:46.160
Hey! You!

307
00:29:47.410 --> 00:29:48.500
Hey. come here!

308
00:29:50.000 --> 00:29:52.306
Out of the water! Out of the water!

309
00:29:52.330 --> 00:29:54.080
Everybody. get outta here! Go!

310
00:29:57.130 --> 00:29:59.526
Rescue station one.
this is sheriff clemmons.

311
00:29:59.550 --> 00:30:02.656
All available fire and
rescue to Patricia's cocktails.

312
00:30:02.680 --> 00:30:04.236
I don't know what the fuck is going on!

313
00:30:04.260 --> 00:30:07.010
Hey! No. ma'am. Back this way!

314
00:30:14.360 --> 00:30:15.360
What?

315
00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:22.620
No. this way. Get back here!

316
00:30:25.530 --> 00:30:26.530
That'll kill 'em.

317
00:31:03.950 --> 00:31:05.160
Come here! Come here.

318
00:31:05.740 --> 00:31:07.370
Out of the water. Stop!

319
00:31:13.120 --> 00:31:14.960
What the fuck happened?

320
00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:20.800
My god.

321
00:31:22.260 --> 00:31:23.720
We were drugged.

322
00:31:25.720 --> 00:31:27.390
It was that goddamn punch.

323
00:31:28.890 --> 00:31:31.180
It was her goddamn punch!

324
00:31:31.770 --> 00:31:33.100
She drugged us!

325
00:31:44.450 --> 00:31:45.450
Patricia?

326
00:31:48.870 --> 00:31:49.870
You okay?

327
00:31:51.660 --> 00:31:52.910
No.

328
00:31:55.870 --> 00:31:57.710
Something bad happened at the party.

329
00:31:59.800 --> 00:32:00.800
It went wrong.

330
00:32:02.130 --> 00:32:04.906
You can file that under
"deal with it the fuck later."

331
00:32:04.930 --> 00:32:05.930
Why don't…

332
00:32:07.430 --> 00:32:10.230
Why don't you just get in with us?

333
00:32:11.390 --> 00:32:12.600
We might need your help.

334
00:32:16.650 --> 00:32:17.650
Come on.

335
00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.056
- What was wrong with him?
- I don't know.

336
00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:36.670
He just sounded scared.

337
00:32:37.250 --> 00:32:38.960
Because he knows something.

338
00:32:47.510 --> 00:32:48.510
Bryce!
